{% set pageTitle = 'Care cards' %}
{% set pageDescription = 'How to use care cards to help users understand the sort of care they need and how quickly they need to act.' %}

{% extends 'includes/layout.njk' %}
{% from 'components/care-card/macro.njk' import careCard %}
{% from 'components/panel/macro.njk' import panel %}
{% from 'includes/design-example.njk' import designExample %}

{% block breadcrumb %}
{{ breadcrumb({
  items: [
    {
      href: "/service-manual/",
      text: "Home"
    }
  ],
  href: "/service-manual/styles-components-patterns",
  text: "Styles, components and patterns"
}) }}
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
    <h1 class="nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-5">{{pageTitle}}</h1>
    <p class="nhsuk-body-l">{{pageDescription}}</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
    <p class="nhsuk-body-l">We have 3 care cards for 3 levels of urgency:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#non-urgent-care-card-blue">non-urgent care card (blue)</a></li>
      <li><a href="#urgent-care-card-red">urgent care card (red)</a></li>
      <li><a href="#emergency-care-card-red-and-black">immediate care card (red and black)</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-full">
    <h2 class="nhsuk-u-margin-top-8" id="non-urgent-care-card-blue">Non-urgent care card (blue)</h2>
    {{ designExample({
      type: 'care-card-non-urgent'
    }) }}
  </div>
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds nhsuk-u-margin-top-8">
    <p>Use this card when you want users to contact their GP or arrange an appointment with a GP or another health professional, like a practice nurse. You can also use it to tell users to go to or get in touch with a clinic, for example for a chlamydia test.</p>
    <p><a href="#how-to-use-care-cards">More about how to use care cards.</a></p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-full">
    <h2 class="nhsuk-u-margin-top-8" id="urgent-care-card-red">Urgent care card (red)</h2>
    {{ designExample({
      type: 'care-card-urgent'
    }) }}
  </div>
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds nhsuk-u-margin-top-8">
    <p>Use this card when you want users to call or visit a GP or hospital urgently. This can include getting urgent care in a walk-in centre or minor injuries centre.</p>
    <p>If appropriate, tell users to ask for an urgent appointment when they ring their GP practice. It can empower them.</p>
    <p><a href="#how-to-use-care-cards">More about how to use care cards.</a></p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-full">
    <h2 class="nhsuk-u-margin-top-8" id="emergency-care-card-red-and-black">Immediate care card (red and black)</h2>
    {{ designExample({
      type: 'care-card-immediate'
    }) }}
  </div>
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds nhsuk-u-margin-top-8">
    <p>Use this card when users need to get emergency help straight away - meaning "now". Tell them to dial 999 or go to their nearest accident and emergency department.</p>
    <p>Where appropriate, include a link to help users find their <a href="http://www.nhs.uk/service-search/Accident-and-emergency-services/LocationSearch/428">nearest hospital accident and emergency (A&amp;E) department</a>.</p>
    <p>Avoid linking to more information about a condition from an emergency care card. If it's an emergency, the important thing is to dial 999 or go to A&amp;E.</p>
    <p>Only use this card for emergencies.</p>

    <h2 class="nhsuk-u-margin-top-8" id="how-to-use-care-cards">How to use care cards</h2>
    <h3>When to use care cards</h3>
    <p>Use care cards to tell users to contact their GP or get medical advice or help. If you want to highlight a key point, use inset text. If you want to warn a user about something, use a warning callout instead.</p>
    <h3>When not to use care cards</h3>
    <p>Don't use care cards:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>in forms or transactions</li>
      <li>for actions which don't help users get one of the 3 levels of care</li>
    </ul>
    <p>If you want:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>to signpost users to the start of a digital service, use an action link - for example, to find a pharmacy</li>
      <li>to point them to another organisation, like a charity, use <a href="/service-manual/styles-components-patterns/inset-text">inset text</a> - or just link from a line of text</li>
      <li>to warn a user about something, use a <a href="/service-manual/styles-components-patterns/warning-callout">warning callout</a> instead</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Research</h2>
    <p>Get in touch to share your research findings if you've used this pattern.</p>

    <h2>Discuss</h2>
    <p>Discuss warning callouts on the <a href="">NHS.UK #standards Slack channel</a> or email the standards team at <a href="">service-manual@nhs.net</a>.</p>

    <div class="nhsuk-review-date">
    <p class="nhsuk-body-s">Updated: <time>January 2019</time></p>
    </div>

    {{ panel({
    "label": "Similar patterns",
    "HTML": "<ul>
              <li><a href='/styles-components-patterns/do-and-dont-lists'>Do and Don't list</a></li>
              <li><a href='/styles-components-patterns/inset-text'>Inset text</a></li>
              <li><a href='/styles-components-patterns/warning-callout'>Warning callout</a></li>
            </ul>"
    }) }}

  </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
